### Area

admin/fine-grained-permissions

### Describe the bug

The valuation tool for fine grained admin permission breaks for resource type "Clients" if you search a client by typing into the field and selecting a client.
Directly selecting a client from the dropdown without searching works.
After typing and selecting a client, only the first character of the clientId is sent, breaking the evaluation.

Payload sent to the authz/resource-server/policy/evaluate Endpoint before searching a client
`{
    "roleIds": [
    ],
    "userId": "e42bd2b6-21c6-423b-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX",
    "resourceType": "Clients",
    "resources": [
        {
            "name": "4430a403-563e-4844-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXX",
            "scopes": [
            ]
        }
    ],
    "entitlements": false,
    "context": {
        "attributes": {
        }
    }
}`

After searching and selecting a client, the following payload is sent:
`{
    "roleIds": [
    ],
    "userId": "e42bd2b6-21c6-423b-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX",
    "resourceType": "Clients",
    "resources": [
        {
            "name": "4",
            "scopes": [
            ]
        }
    ],
    "entitlements": false,
    "context": {
        "attributes": {
        }
    }
}`

### Version

26.3.1

### Regression

- [ ] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

Selecting a client after searching still submits the correct, full clientId

### Actual behavior

After searching a client, ClientId is cut after the first char

### How to Reproduce?

In the evaluation tool, select a user, select "Resource type": "Clients" and start typing into the "Client" field to filter for clients.
Select a client and press evaluate.
The request sent to the Server only contains the first char of the clientId of the selected client.

### Anything else?

_No response_
